Two persons have been killed by suspected herdsmen near Ikyungwa Tombo ward , near Ayilamo, Logo Local Government area in Benue State. The incident happened about 4 pm on Monday, along Ikyungwa â€“ Ayilamo road, The Nation gathered. An eyewitness Zuzu told our correspondent thaa two persons, a woman and man, were returning from farm on motorcycle when the herdsmen attacked and shot them.. He identified the deceased as Bem Uhembe and Mungwa Zuzu, all from Tse Ibor. He said they were returning to Ayilamo town where they spent the night because their settlement had been taken over by herdsmen. On the road between Ikyungwa and Ayilamo, herdsmen who laid ambush, open fire and killed them at the spot.   BREAKING: APC Govs propose Tinubu, four others for primary     All set for APC presidential primary     PHOTOS: All set for APC presidential primary   The corpses have been deposited at Ayilamo mortuary. Tombo ward, a farming settlement, has come under sustained attacks from suspected herdsmen since 2016. The inhabitants are spread on Bank of River Benue about 200,000 square meters. The residents produce massive rice, soybeans , cassava, guinea corn and yams. . The Nation reports there is no police station in Tombo ward while the 72 Special Battalion Forces stationed in Anyibe to wade off armed herdsmen crossing from Nasaarawa State to attack and kill harmless farmers in Tse Ibor, Tse Dzungwe, Tse Gbeleve and other settlements were withdrawn two months. Benue Police Command said it was yet to get the information on the killings.